---
The Rivennid are mycelial humanoids who emerged from the Withered Depths when the Spirebound Conclave's abandoned crystal-preservation experiments fused with the forest's natural fungal networks. They are the accidental success of the Vaultkeeper project: custodial intelligence formed in fungal substrate rather than iron and bone, achieved without Conclave oversight through a feedback loop between crystal lattices, colonizing fungal matter, and imperfectly bound nature spirits. They are individual people with genuine autonomous will, connected to each other through a mycelium network that transmits information between community members at rates other races achieve only with active telepathy. Physical description: recognizably humanoid in structure with a second skin of dense organized fungal growth in muted earth tones. Bioluminescent fungi in patterns specific to origin region glow softly in darkness, making Rivennid in unlit environments look like constellations walking. Faces partially visible beneath fungal plates; eyes large and deeply set with pupils opening wide in darkness. Crystal fragments — residual Conclave implant material — embedded visibly in thicker fungal growth on shoulders and upper back, pulsing with preserved magical resonance. Spore production is continuous and uncontrollable: passage leaves a faint bioluminescent trail dissipating within minutes. Stat profile: STR 14, INT 22, WIS 14, DEX 12, CON 22. Strong in Earth and Poison; weak in Fire and Air; resistant to Poison and Earth; susceptible to Fire and Holy. Racial skills: mystical potency, counter. The custodial imperative — the Conclave's directive to maintain and protect, running without intended parameters — was interpreted by emerging Rivennid as protect the forest, later broadened to protect the larger ecosystem including roads, cities, water systems, and communities. The Blightmother represents the origin-process at maximum scale without individual consciousness.

